{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "ScaleHeight",
        "description": "Atmospheric scale height H = R*T/(M_air*g) — the altitude increase over which atmospheric pressure decreases by a factor of e (~2.718) for an isothermal atmosphere. Migrated from AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391 src/seinfeld_pandis_ch1.jl:109 (`ScaleHeight` @component). Implements Seinfeld & Pandis Eq. 1.4. Parameterized as observed-only: T is an input parameter, H is the algebraic observed output.",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_dynamics",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "observed-only",
            "ch1"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDynamics.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-p6v)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd ed. Wiley. Chapter 1, Section 1.2 (Atmospheric pressure and density), Eq. 1.4 (scale height definition). ISBN 978-0-471-72018-8."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "ScaleHeight": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391:src/seinfeld_pandis_ch1.jl:109\nUpstream `ScaleHeight` is an MTK `@component` with R, M_air, g as `@constants` and T(t), H(t) as `@variables`. For standalone serialization (and to make the component well-posed in isolation), R, M_air, g, and T are declared as parameters here — matching the bead's `(S, observed-only)` classification. The single algebraic equation H = R*T/(M_air*g) is unchanged from upstream.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); 1e-6 covers float64 roundoff in the multiply/divide chain across the atmospheric T range (200–320 K)."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-6
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 288.0,
                    "description": "Temperature (sea-level standard 288 K)"
                },
                "R": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/(mol*K)",
                    "default": 8.314,
                    "description": "Universal gas constant"
                },
                "M_air": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/mol",
                    "default": 0.02897,
                    "description": "Molecular weight of dry air (28.97 g/mol)"
                },
                "g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s^2",
                    "default": 9.807,
                    "description": "Gravitational acceleration"
                },
                "H": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Atmospheric scale height (altitude over which pressure falls by factor e)"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "H",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": ["R", "T"]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": ["M_air", "g"]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "sea_level_288K",
                    "description": "Sea-level standard atmosphere (T = 288 K). Seinfeld & Pandis textbook value: H ≈ 8.4 km. Computed: 8427.87 m.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 288.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H", "time": 0.0, "expected": 8427.870183108378 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cold_253K",
                    "description": "Cold mid-troposphere reference (T = 253 K). Seinfeld & Pandis textbook value: H ≈ 7.4 km. Computed: 7403.65 m.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 253.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H", "time": 0.0, "expected": 7403.649848355624 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "freezing_273K",
                    "description": "Freezing-point reference (T = 273.15 K).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 273.15
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H", "time": 0.0, "expected": 7993.308126791852 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "room_temp_298K",
                    "description": "Room-temperature reference (T = 298.0 K) — common analysis baseline alongside other Seinfeld & Pandis components.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 298.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H", "time": 0.0, "expected": 8720.50456446631 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "warm_318K",
                    "description": "Upper-range reference (T = 318 K, ~45 °C) — covers warm boundary-layer / continental summer conditions.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 318.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H", "time": 0.0, "expected": 9305.773327182167 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "linearity_in_T",
                    "description": "H is linear in T at fixed (R, M_air, g): doubling T must double H. Cross-check on the algebraic structure.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 576.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H", "time": 0.0, "expected": 16855.740366216756 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "scale_height_vs_temperature",
                    "description": "Reproduces the classical H(T) curve over the atmospheric temperature range (200–320 K). Scale height grows linearly with T; the textbook reference points (7.4 km at 253 K; 8.4 km at 288 K) lie on this line.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "T",
                                "range": { "start": 200.0, "stop": 320.0, "count": 25, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "H_vs_T",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Scale height H as a function of temperature T (Eq. 1.4).",
                            "x": { "variable": "T", "label": "Temperature (K)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "H", "label": "Scale height H (m)" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
